# Arrays

Arrays are fundamental data structures that store elements in contiguous memory locations. They provide O(1) access to elements by index.

## Key Concepts

- **Fixed size** (in many languages)
- **Contiguous memory**
- **O(1) access by index**
- **O(n) insertion/deletion**

## Common Operations

```javascript
// Array operations
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

// Access - O(1)
arr[0]; // 1

// Push - O(1) amortized
arr.push(6);

// Pop - O(1)
arr.pop();

// Slice - O(n)
arr.slice(1, 3); // [2, 3]
```

